{
  "info": {
    "name": "Deltameta — Auth API",
    "description": "Complete Auth & Organization Hierarchy API collection for the Deltameta backend.\n\n**Quick Start:**\n1. Run `Register User` — a JWT token is auto-saved to the `token` variable.\n2. All subsequent requests use that token automatically via the collection-level Authorization header.\n3. Use `Login` to get a fresh token at any time.\n\n**Variables (set in Collection → Variables tab):**\n- `base_url` — default: `http://localhost:8000`\n- `token`    — auto-populated by Register / Login scripts",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "user_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "org_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "second_org_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "domain_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "team_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "child_team_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "role_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "policy_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "subscription_id", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Register User",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/register",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "register"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"John Doe\",\n  \"display_name\": \"John\",\n  \"email\": \"john@example.com\",\n  \"username\": \"johndoe\",\n  \"password\": \"Test@1234\",\n  \"org_name\": \"Acme Corp\"\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "description": "Creates a new user and a default organization.\n\n- `org_name` is optional — auto-generated from the user's name if omitted.\n- First user of an org is automatically an org admin (`is_admin: true`).\n- Returns the created `UserResponse`.\n\n**Success:** `201 Created`\n**Errors:** `409` — email or username already taken, `422` — validation error."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Response has user id', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('id'));",
              "pm.test('Response has email', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('email'));",
              "pm.test('Has default_org_id', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('default_org_id'));",
              "if(body.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('user_id', body.id);",
              "if(body.default_org_id) pm.collectionVariables.set('org_id', body.default_org_id);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Login",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "login"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"login\": \"john@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Test@1234\"\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "description": "Authenticates a user by email or username and returns a JWT token.\n\n- `login` can be the user's **email** or **username**.\n- The JWT token is automatically saved to the `token` collection variable for all subsequent requests.\n\n**Success:** `200 OK` → `{ access_token, token_type, expires_in }`\n**Errors:** `401` — wrong credentials, `403` — account locked/inactive."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "if (body.access_token) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', body.access_token);",
              "    console.log('Token saved to collection variable.');",
              "}",
              "pm.test('access_token present', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('access_token'));",
              "pm.test('token_type is bearer', () => pm.expect(body.token_type).to.eql('bearer'));",
              "pm.test('expires_in is a number', () => pm.expect(body.expires_in).to.be.a('number'));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Get Current User (me)",
      "request": {
        "auth": { "type": "inherit" },
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/me",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "me"]
        },
        "description": "Returns the profile of the currently authenticated user.\n\n**Requires:** Bearer token (auto-set from Login).\n\n**Success:** `200 OK` → `UserResponse`\n**Errors:** `401` — missing/invalid token, `403` — inactive account."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('user_id', body.id);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('org_id', body.default_org_id || body.org_id);",
              "pm.test('Response has email', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('email'));",
              "pm.test('Has default_org_id', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('default_org_id'));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Update Profile (me)",
      "request": {
        "auth": { "type": "inherit" },
        "method": "PUT",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/me",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "me"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"John Updated\",\n  \"display_name\": \"Johnny\",\n  \"description\": \"Senior Data Engineer\",\n  \"image\": \"https://example.com/avatar.png\"\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "description": "Updates the current user's profile fields. All fields are optional — only send what you want to change.\n\nUse `default_org_id` field to switch your active organization context (must be an org you belong to).\n\n**Requires:** Bearer token.\n\n**Success:** `200 OK` → Updated `UserResponse`\n**Errors:** `401/403`."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('Name updated', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().name).to.eql('John Updated');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4b. Switch Default Org",
      "request": {
        "auth": { "type": "inherit" },
        "method": "PUT",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "me"] },
        "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"default_org_id\": \"{{second_org_id}}\"\n}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
        "description": "Switch active organization. Run after creating a second org and setting {{second_org_id}}."
      },
      "event": [{"listen":"test","script":{"type":"text/javascript","exec":["pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));","pm.test('default_org_id updated', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().default_org_id).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('second_org_id')));"]}}]
    },
    {
      "name": "4c. List My Orgs",
      "request": {
        "auth": { "type": "inherit" },
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/me/orgs", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "me", "orgs"] },
        "description": "Returns all organizations the current user belongs to."
      },
      "event": [{"listen":"test","script":{"type":"text/javascript","exec":["pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));","pm.test('Returns array', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array'));","pm.test('At least 1 org', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().length).to.be.greaterThan(0));"]}}]
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Refresh Token",
      "request": {
        "auth": { "type": "inherit" },
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/refresh",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "refresh"]
        },
        "description": "Issues a new JWT token with a fresh expiry using the current valid token.\n\nUseful for extending sessions without re-authenticating.\n\n**Requires:** Bearer token.\n\n**Success:** `200 OK` → `{ access_token, token_type, expires_in }`"
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "if (body.access_token) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', body.access_token);",
              "    console.log('Token refreshed and saved.');",
              "}",
              "pm.test('New token returned', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('access_token'));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Logout",
      "request": {
        "auth": { "type": "inherit" },
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/logout",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "logout"]
        },
        "description": "Instructs the client to discard the token. No server-side blacklist is maintained in this default implementation — token invalidation is client-side.\n\n**Requires:** Bearer token.\n\n**Success:** `200 OK` → `{ message }`"
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('Message returned', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('message');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "7. Forgot Password",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/forgot-password",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "forgot-password"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"john@example.com\"\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "description": "Initiates a password reset flow for the given email address.\n\n**Stub implementation** — always returns success to prevent user enumeration. Production flow: generates a token, stores it, and sends a reset email.\n\n**No auth required.**\n\n**Success:** `200 OK` → `{ message }`"
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('Message returned', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('message'));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "8. Reset Password",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/reset-password",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "reset-password"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"reset_token\": \"<token-from-email>\",\n  \"new_password\": \"NewPass@5678\"\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "description": "Resets the user's password using a token received via email.\n\n**Stub** — currently returns `501 Not Implemented`. Will validate the token from DB, update the hashed password, and invalidate the token in production.\n\n**No auth required.**\n\n**Expected (stub):** `501 Not Implemented`"
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 501 (stub)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(501));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "9. Get Auth Config (org admin)",
      "request": {
        "auth": { "type": "inherit" },
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/config",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "config"]
        },
        "description": "Returns the JWT and lockout configuration for the current user's organization.\n\n**Requires:** Org admin token (`is_admin: true`).\n\n**Success:** `200 OK` → `AuthConfigResponse`\n```json\n{\n  \"org_id\": \"...\",\n  \"jwt_expiry_minutes\": 60,\n  \"max_failed_attempts\": 5,\n  \"lockout_duration_minutes\": 15,\n  \"sso_provider\": \"default\",\n  \"updated_at\": \"...\"\n}\n```\n**Errors:** `403` — not an org admin."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Has jwt_expiry_minutes', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('jwt_expiry_minutes'));",
              "pm.test('Has max_failed_attempts', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('max_failed_attempts'));",
              "pm.test('Has lockout_duration_minutes', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('lockout_duration_minutes'));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "10. Update Auth Config (org admin)",
      "request": {
        "auth": { "type": "inherit" },
        "method": "PUT",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/config",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "config"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"jwt_expiry_minutes\": 120,\n  \"max_failed_attempts\": 10,\n  \"lockout_duration_minutes\": 30\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "description": "Updates the JWT token expiry and lockout policy for the organization.\n\n**Requires:** Org admin token (`is_admin: true`).\n\n| Field | Description | Min | Max |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `jwt_expiry_minutes` | Token validity in minutes | 1 | 10080 (7 days) |\n| `max_failed_attempts` | Failed logins before lockout | 1 | 100 |\n| `lockout_duration_minutes` | Lockout window in minutes | 1 | 1440 (24h) |\n\n**Success:** `200 OK` → Updated `AuthConfigResponse`\n**Errors:** `403` — not an org admin, `422` — value out of range."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('jwt_expiry_minutes updated to 120', () => pm.expect(body.jwt_expiry_minutes).to.eql(120));",
              "pm.test('max_failed_attempts updated to 10', () => pm.expect(body.max_failed_attempts).to.eql(10));",
              "pm.test('lockout_duration_minutes updated to 30', () => pm.expect(body.lockout_duration_minutes).to.eql(30));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
